Brute Force Solution of Travelling salesman problem.

The program takes the input the 'n' number of nodes. It then constructs a hamiltonian graph of n nodes starting from node 0 and assigns random distance between the nodes.
It then calculates all the possbile tours and the cost associated with each tour. At the same time records the minimum cost and tour.
The time complexity of this approach is very high: O(n!)
The time that program takes to execute increases factorially as the n increases. For n>15 it takes very long time. Hence, other approaches have to devised to computer shortest path for n>20.


